The paper proposes a novel deep learning architecture for crowd counting in images, which involves the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and attention mechanisms. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of machine learning techniques such as multi-scale feature fusion and joint training, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) research. The paper also involves the use of image processing techniques such as density map generation, which falls under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of robotics applications such as crowd monitoring, which falls under the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category.
